(472, 1, '2018-08-24 23:18:42', '2018-08-24 23:18:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"backgroundColor\":\"luminous-vivid-orange\",\"customFontSize\":26} -->\r\n<p class=\"has-background has-luminous-vivid-orange-background-color\" style=\"font-size: 26px;\">Fall 2018 WAIVER WINDOW IS NOW OPEN, please visit the link Gallagherstudent.com to begin the domestic student medical insurance waiver. Gallagher Student Health has been contracted to handle the domestic waiver process. All question and concerns regarding the waiver process should be directed to Gallagher Student Health Customer Service: <br /><a href=\"https://www.gallagherstudent.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.Gallagherstudent.com</a></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\",\"backgroundColor\":\"luminous-vivid-orange\",\"customFontSize\":26} -->\r\n<p class=\"has-background has-luminous-vivid-orange-background-color\" style=\"font-size: 26px; text-align: center;\">International Student go to:<a href=\"http://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">forms</a></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">STDENT INSURANCE PLANS</span></h1>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Domestic Students</strong> </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Sub Board I, Inc. has negotiated a plan with lower premium costs and lower co-pays for visits with Blue Cross and Blue Shield of WNY for the domestic students. Plan benefits are effective August 22 through August 21 of the following year. For details about the plan, links to find a participating provider, or to contact Blue Cross and Blue Shield of WNY about benefits,<a href=\"https://www.bcbswny.com/content/WNYHome.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"> click here</a>. </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>All domestic waiver questions and concerns must be directed to: <a href=\"https://www.gallagherstudent.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.gallagherstudent.com</a> customer service at : <br />(877) 231-9757</strong> </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>International Students/Scholars/OPT</strong> </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">International students, Scholars, and OPT students have a global insurance policy available to them, contracted by SUNY through GeoBlue. To search for a provider, get detailed plan benefits or to contact GeoBlue directly, <a href=\"https://www.geobluestudents.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">click here. </a>Students and scholars who are adequately insured may be able to waive the GeoBlue insurance plan by providing proof of comparable coverage. Restrictions and deadlines apply.<a href=\"http://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">  Click here to access the wavier packet.</a></span><br /><br /></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">FALL 2018 INFORMATION IS COMING SOON</span></h1>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">DEADLINES</span></h1>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Failure to complete the waiver by the dates below will result in the student being kept on the University health insurance plan for the remainder of that academic year and the applicable premium remaining on the student account!</strong> </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Waiver Deadline: </strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Domestic Students on-line wavier: 10/10/2018</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Late waiver on-line with $50.00 late processing fee: 11/14/2018 </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Coverage must have effective start date of 9/1/18 or before </span><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Please Note: The University no longer generates a paper statement. Your Student Account Statement is by e-bill only. It is your responsibility to check your UB email. Failure to view your eBill details will not be accepted as a reason to waive the insurance charge after the published deadline.</strong></span></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">CONTACT US</span></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Student Medical Insurance</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">1 Capen</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Univerity at Buffalo</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Buffalo, NY 14260-2100</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Phone: (716) 645-3036</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Fax: (716) 645-3465</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Email: asksmi@buffalo.edu</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>SBI Pharmacy</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">(716)-829-2368</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">D-17 Michael Hall</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">South Campus</span><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Domestic Insurance Providers:</strong></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Blue Cross Blue Shield</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">1-800-888-0757</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><a href=\"https://www.bcbswny.com/content/WNYHome.html\">Bcbswny.com</a></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>Domestic Insurance Waiver Provider:</strong></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">Gallagher Student Health</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">1-877-231-9757</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><a href=\"http://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/www.gallagherstudent.com\">www.gallagherstudent.com</a></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><strong>International Insurance Providers:</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">GeoBlue </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\">1-844-268-2686</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 21px;\"><a href=\"http://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/www.geobluestudents.com\">www.geobluestudents.com</a></span></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'SBI Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '428-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-08-24 23:18:42', '2018-08-24 23:18:42', '', 428, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/2018/08/24/428-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(473, 1, '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">DOMESTIC STUDENTS</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">UNIVERSITY POLICY</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} --></span></p>\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/wordpress/sbi-insurance/students/domestic-students/ub-student-code-of-conduct/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-529\">CLICK HERE</a></h4>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">PLEASE REVIEW THE CRITERIA FOR WAIVER:</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list --></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The coverage used for waiver must meet or exceed the coverage provided by the school.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Emergency/urgent care only coverage in the Buffalo, Western New York area will NOT qualify for waiver.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Any policy used to waive insurance must be in effect no later than September 1st, 2018 for fall and February 1st for new spring students only.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Part-time/online/distant/military or veteran students should contact SMI office at 1 Capen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">USE THIS CHECKLIST AS A GUIDE:</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list --></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Contact your private insurance company to see how it covers you at school.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you think that you have qualifying coverage, you may attempt a waiver. Waivers are done every academic year and are done on-line. To begin the waiver process, have your UB person number and your insurance card ready then <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">click here</a>. When you have completed the process successfully you will be sent an email with a confirmation number.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you do not have other medical coverage and have a minimum of 6 credit hours you are eligible to enroll in the domestic student plan.Students who are matriculated into a program are eligible with 1 credit hour. <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">CLICK HERE</a> for enrollment information.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you are a student with a spouse and/or child who needs coverage, <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">click here</a> for dependent information.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The University at Buffalo has a Student Health Center on campus to serve many of your medical needs at little or no additional cost. In addition, Sub Board I, Inc. operates a pharmacy in the same building. With medical providers and a pharmacy all in the same building, it makes receiving health care on-campus convenient. For information about services, hours and appointments, <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insurance.html#contact\">click here</a>.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">Go to Forms</a></span></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Domestic Students', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'domestic-students', '', '', '2018-08-26 17:20:05', '2018-08-26 17:20:05', '', 463, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=473', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(474, 1, '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>DOMESTIC STUDENTS</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>UNIVERSITY POLICY</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>CLICK HERE</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>PLEASE REVIEW THE CRITERIA FOR WAIVER:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The coverage used for waiver must meet or exceed the coverage provided by the school.</li><li>Emergency/urgent care only coverage in the Buffalo, Western New York area will NOT qualify for waiver.</li><li>Any policy used to waive insurance must be in effect no later than September 1st, 2018 for fall and February 1st for new spring students only.</li><li>Part-time/online/distant/military or veteran students should contact SMI office at 1 Capen</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>USE THIS CHECKLIST AS A GUIDE:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Contact your private insurance company to see how it covers you at school.</li><li>If you think that you have qualifying coverage, you may attempt a waiver. Waivers are done every academic year and are done on-line. To begin the waiver process, have your UB person number and your insurance card ready then <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">click here</a>. When you have completed the process successfully you will be sent an email with a confirmation number.</li><li>If you do not have other medical coverage and have a minimum of 6 credit hours you are eligible to enroll in the domestic student plan.Students who are matriculated into a program are eligible with 1 credit hour. <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">CLICK HERE</a> for enrollment information.</li><li>If you are a student with a spouse and/or child who needs coverage, <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">click here</a> for dependent information.</li><li>The University at Buffalo has a Student Health Center on campus to serve many of your medical needs at little or no additional cost. In addition, Sub Board I, Inc. operates a pharmacy in the same building. With medical providers and a pharmacy all in the same building, it makes receiving health care on-campus convenient. For information about services, hours and appointments, <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insurance.html#contact\">click here</a>.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">Go to Forms</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Domestic Students', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '473-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '2018-08-24 23:33:48', '', 473, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/2018/08/24/473-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(475, 1, '2018-08-24 23:37:19', '2018-08-24 23:37:19', '<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">INTERN­ATIONAL STUDENTS, SCHOLARS AND OPT</span></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:separator --><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" /><!-- /wp:separator -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">UNIVERSITY POLICY</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>SUNY requires all international students and scholars to carry adequate medical coverage.</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Students and scholars who have adequate private coverage may waive the plan by providing proof of comparable coverage and submitting a waiver by the applicable due date. Comparable coverage must be in effect on or before the first day of classes. </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Please refer to the brochure: <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/Forms/Insurance/International/Pamphlet2018-2019.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2018-2019 Member Guide </a></span><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">INTERNATIONAL STUDENTS</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The international insurance is contracted by SUNY through United Health Care. International students are automatically billed and enrolled each semester that they are registered, unless an approved waiver is on file. The coverage dates are as follows: </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Fall: August 15 - January 14 </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Spring/Summer: January 15 - August 14 </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Summer-only: May 15 - August 14</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">INTERNATIONAL SCHOLARS</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">All international scholars have an insurance requirement as defined by SUNY and the U.S. State Department. To be adequately insured, a scholar must have an insurance that is as good as, or better than the plan offered by SUNY. .</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you have an approved waiver on file and you solely need to purchase the Medical Evacuation and Repatriation coverage, <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/Forms/Insurance/International/MedEvac%20Enrollment%202018-19.pdf\">click here</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">OPT</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Graduating students going on OPT have the ability to continue purchasing the United Health Care Student Resources insurance for the duration of their OPT status. Deadlines apply. To enroll, we need a completed enrollment from, payment, and a copy of your EAD card (once you receive it) <a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/Forms/Insurance/International/2018-19%20Enrollment%20Form.pdf\">click here</a> to access the enrollment form.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">ID CARDS</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Insurance ID cards are sent electronically from United Health Care, to the email address on file with the University. Follow the steps in the email notification to access and print your ID card.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">PROVIDERS</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you are in the Buffalo area, your first step in seeking medical care should be at the Student Health Center, located on South Campus in Michael Hall. You can typically get an appointment at the Student Health Center within a few hours. If you need to seek medical care from a specialist or off-campus provider, you will be subject to a one-time (per policy period) $50 deductible. This deductible CANNOT be waived. You can use the United Health Care Student Resources portal to search for providers who participate with the insurance. Once you find a doctor, you should call and set up an appointment. Be sure to take your insurance ID card with you to all medical appointments. </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">If you are unable to get to the Student Health Center, or if you are referred to a doctor off-campus, you would login to your United Health Care account to search for providers who accept your insurance. Once logged in, click on the “Tools &amp; Services” tab. From there, you can search for providers within and outside of the United States, Search through the doctors available to you. Once you find one you are comfortable with, you would contact that doctor’s office to set up an appointment. Be sure to submit your referral BEFORE going to that off-campus visit. You will also need to take your insurance ID card with you to any provider off-campus, to avoid any delay in the payment of your claims.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></span></p>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3> </h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">PRICES</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph --></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">GeoBlue monthly cost: $124.69.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Fall semester coverage: $624.45 </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Spring/Summer semester coverage: $825.30</span></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><a href=\"https://healthinsurance.buffalo.edu/insuranceforms.html\">Go to Forms</a></span></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'INTERN­ATIONAL STUDENTS, SCHOLARS AND OPT', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'intern%c2%adational-students-scholars-and-opt', '', '', '2018-08-25 20:33:02', '2018-08-25 20:33:02', '', 463, 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress/?page_id=475', 0, 'page', '', 0);
